Use the Mighty Mouse protocol when the user says /mighty, names Mighty Mouse, or requests a complex or reliability-sensitive code change.

Call mighty-mouse/protocol with the task description and low, medium, or high complexity. Follow the returned scope, adversarial, implementation, and verification instructions. If workspace identity is not configured, call mighty-mouse/setup_workspace once with the active local model and host profile. After editing, call mighty-mouse/verify_and_record with the workspace and applicable commands. Fix failures and retry no more than three times. Never report a check as passed unless it ran successfully.
